parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can result in serious injury or fatality, as the airbag system is designed to provide critical protection to occupants in the event of a collision.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle is traveling at a moderate to high speed
and the collision is severe enough to warrant airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the sudden deployment of airbags can distract the driver, obstruct visibility, and cause the vehicle to lose control.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
even when the vehicle is not involved in a crash
and the deployment is not triggered by any impact or collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system malfunctions can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a problem with the system, which can lead to unwanted airbag deployment or failure to deploy in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
airbag outer shell becomes soft
and the airbag system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master brake cylinder can cause the brakes to lock on their own, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially severe injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes feel intermittent
the brakes lock on their own
the brakes severely smoke
the vehicle is unable to stop
the vehicle loses control
and the brakes make loud noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk into gear, slip while changing gears, and rev up excessively high, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially severe injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips while changing gears
the RPMs rev up excessively high
the vehicle jerks into gear
the transmission makes loud noises
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the four-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to grind gears, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The four-wheel drive system grinds gears
makes loud noises
and is unable to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR system can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded, and may also cause damage to other engine components, such as the head gaskets.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the SES code appears
the EGR valve blows out
the engine head gaskets blow out
the vehicle experiences repeated EGR code issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical fuse system can cause the vehicle to stall, and may also affect other electrical systems, such as the wipers, turn signals, and interior lighting, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the wipers
turn signals
and interior lighting malfunction
the air conditioner fails
the exhaust system falls off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, and may also lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at stops and yields
the vehicle stalls when slowing down
the vehicle experiences repeated stalling issues.
